               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; &#xD;
the word mǝʿǝraf;&#xD;
six lines (both columns) of the incipit page of each text (fols. 3rab, 36rab, 54rab, 85rab), divided into three groups, alternating with black lines;&#xD;
some lines (1-3) within “short postscript” of the each text;&#xD;
two initial lines of the list of “tituli” for the Gospel of John (fol. 108rb [ls. 8-9]);&#xD;
some extra notes, indicating the chapter titles, and some of the lines above and below them;&#xD;
Ethiopic numerals indicating the “tituli”;&#xD;
the horizontal dashes above and below Ethiopic numerals; &#xD;
elements of the punctuation signs;&#xD;
names of the scribe (fol. 108va, ls. 14-15; 20-21) and donors (fol. 108va, ls. 8, 9, 10).</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Concerning the short postscripts, cp. R. ZUURMOND, Novum Testamentum Aethiopice: the Synoptic Gospels, Part I: General Introduction, Part II: Edition of the Gospel of Mark, Stuttgart 1989 (AeF 27), 29-31.</note>
                     <note>The list of “Tituli” for the Gospel of Matthew is missing.</note>
                     <note>In the list of “Tituli” for the Gospel of Mark (fol. 35ra [l.1] – 35rb [l.23]), the titles are 48, but the ultimate number is 50 (፶): after 31 (፴፩), the numbers 32 (፴፪) and 33 (፴፫) are missing; the numbering resumes from 34 (፴፬) and goes until 50.</note>
                  </msItem>
